<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-39-0363 </DOCNO><TEXT>In order to explain the large discrepancy between the measured transversecoherent tune shifts and analytical ones in a short bunch in PETRA, theeffects of the closed orbit distortion y/sub co/ and the dispersion etaon a beam instability is studied with a two-particle model. It followsthe result which supports Kohaupt's previous results; they hardly contributeto real tune shift, while the momentum dependence of the wake force canmake a beam unstable, with the growth rate which is proportional to theproduct of y/sub co/ and eta.</TEXT></DOC>